# SEO regression operations (RVA)

Use this workflow for any route, sitemap, robots, canonical, redirect, or metadata change.

## Pre-merge gate (required)

1. Run `npm run seo:audit:sitemap` for production origin and ensure zero issues.
2. Verify changed URLs:
 - first-hop status is intentional (200 for canonical pages, 301/308 for legacy aliases)
 - destination returns 200
 - canonical is self-referencing on canonical pages
3. If a URL is redirected, remove it from sitemap and keep only final canonical destination.
4. Check for internal links to legacy aliases (`/home`, `/service-areas-locations/*`, etc.) and replace with canonical URLs.

## Post-merge checks (within 48 hours)

1. Inspect changed URLs in Google Search Console URL Inspection.
2. Re-fetch `https://www.richvalleyadventures.com/sitemap.xml` and confirm only canonical URLs are present.
3. Confirm `robots.txt` still allows indexable sections and sitemap line is correct.
4. Record what changed, what was validated, and open issues.

## Weekly SEO health check

Track and compare week-over-week:

- Indexed pages count
- Not indexed pages count
- Newly appeared issue types
- Regressed issue types that were previously resolved

If not-indexed count increases week-over-week, pause new route/page additions until regression cause is identified and fixed.

## Marketing/content gate for new pages

Do not add new URLs to sitemap until all are true:

- at least 400 words of meaningful page copy
- unique title and meta description
- one clear H1
- schema markup present where applicable
- at least 2 internal links from existing indexed pages

Keep slug stable after publish. If changed, create a permanent redirect from old URL to new URL.
